<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="465" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">865.857 An 2/95½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hot Springs, Va.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">24 December, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I am not sure whether I
                            am encouraged or not by this,<note n="81" xml:id="d465fn1">Memorandum by
                                the Secretary of State, Dec. 21, 1915, <ref target="#pg_503">p.
                                    503</ref>.</note> but I am clear that you said the right things
                            to the Baron and that it was very wise to make him see the position of
                            the United States without any penumbra about the edges of the
                            statement.</p>
                        <p>Cordially and faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>